        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 7:19PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 719 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Hurst, or 7 miles east
of Blue Ridge, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Blue Ridge, Morganton, Dial, Hemp, Hurst, and Loving.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
north central Georgia. A Severe Thunderstorm Watch also remains in
effect until midnight EDT for north central Georgia.</instruction>
